verbose_text: The current study has shown that, in the model group, the mRNA expression of NF-kappaB, TNF-alpha, IkappaBalpha, and IKKbeta of GES-1 cell lines increased significantly, and the protein concentrations of them in GES-1 supernatant also increased remarkably, while different doses of V. axillare downregulated these factors in GES-1 and supernatant to various degrees.
